  "details": "Open ISES Tickets before 3.44.2 contains a reflected cross-site scripting vulnerability in search.php that allows authenticated attackers to inject arbitrary JavaScript by passing an unsanitized value through the frm_query POST parameter directly into an HTML input field VALUE attribute. Attackers can craft a malicious request containing a JavaScript payload in the frm_query parameter that executes in the victim's browser when submitted.",
